Package de.hshl.obj.loader.objects Description

Classes which are used to represent the OBJ file after loading.

A Mesh is just the plain geometry. A Surface is a Mesh with a Material. A MeshObject is a named entity from the OBJ file which contains only geometry. A SurfaceObject is a named entity from the OBJ file which contains geometry and a Material.
Author:
Johannes Vollmer
See Also:
